ref: 938 aṣṭamaṅgala n. ʻ a collection of eight lucky things ʼ lex. [aṣṭāˊ, maṅgalá -- ]
Pa. aṭṭhamaṅgala -- ʻ having eight auspicious signs ʼ;
Pk. aṭṭhamaṁgala -- m.n. ʻ a collection of them ʼ;
M. aṭhã̄gūḷ, ˚guḷẽ, ˚gḷẽ n. ʻ auspicious ceremony performed in the eighth month of gestation to cleanse the foetus from sins of previous births ʼ, aṭhãgūḷ, ˚guḷā ʻ born in the eighth month ʼ.
